s and ages of Kerala are one of the museum's greatest attractions. The entrance cost is INR 20 per person. The surrounding area is rich and green. 6. Shanmugam Beach in Trivandrum Shanmugam Beach is a beautiful beach located near the city airport. This beach with pure blue sea and white sand is a great location to calm and enjoy the ethereal surroundings. The beach is very clean and has maintained its natural beauty, making it one of the greatest spots to visit in Trivandrum. On the shore, there is also a little Devi shrine. The sunset views from the beach are truly exceptional and enchanting. The peaceful beach is pretty long and quite attractive. The nicest thing about this beach is that it is not as crowded as some of the city's other famous beaches, except around sunset, when many people come here to take in the breathtaking sunset views. 7. Vellayani Lake in Trivandrum Vellayani Lake is the biggest lake in Trivandrum and one of the greatest Trivandrum tourist attractions. The lake provides stunning views of the hamlet and the backwaters, making it a terrific site to visit. Fishing lovers can also test their skills at this lake. It's a great spot for a family picnic. This lake, located in the city's rural sector, is home to white ducks and lotus blossoms. The magnificent surroundings of the lake will inspire you and make you want to spend time enjoying this wonderful lake. There are numerous things to do in Trivandrum, including boating on this lake. 8. Veli Tourist Village in Trivandrum Veli Tourist Village, one of the greatest places to visit in Trivandrum, is an exquisite picnic location nestled beside the lake amid ethereal surroundings. The property includes a stunning garden loaded with vibrant flowers and carefully kept. Veli Tourist Village is undoubtedly a peaceful area to spend quality time surrounded by gorgeous natural lush green. There is some equipment and play places for children, as well as boat trips on the lake. In the Village, visitors may also go horseback riding and participate in sports. 9. Magic Planet in Trivandrum It is a museum with a very unusual concept, focusing on magic, and is a whole for children in Trivandrum. It claims to be the world's first magical themed park and is quickly becoming a popular tourist attraction in Kerala. The museum has a wonderful collection of street magic, performances, and tricks from many books, including The Indian Mango Mystery and The Indian Basket Trick. The magical planet will undoubtedly cast a spell on you, leaving behind the beginnings of wizards and the desire for magic. 10. Planetarium in Trivandrum Priyadarshini Planetarium is, without a doubt, one of the top locations to visit in Trivandrum for people who are fascinated by the universe and wish to learn more about it. Priyadarshini Planetarium first opened to the public in 1994 and has been extremely popular. The planetarium is equipped with a GM-11 starfield projector, which allows you to observe the fascinating universe of planets and stars through its projection. 11. Akkulam Lake in Trivandrum Akkulam Lake, a calm lake in Akkulam, Trivandrum, is ideal for nature enthusiasts. This lake, surrounded by vegetation, is for people who want to visit a tranquil area where they may rest amidst nature and make their Trivandrum sightseeing a must-see. The boat ride you may do with your loved one or alone will highlight your vacation to Akkulam Lake. Take a boat trip and enjoy the picture-perfect sunset. If you're searching for a rejuvenating getaway following a long day, Akkulam Lake has all you need! 12. Anchuthengu Fort in Trivandrum The English East India Company erected this fort in the 16th century, roughly 32 kilometres from Trivandrum Central Railway Station. It was also the East Indian Company's initial colony in Kerala and one of the Company's most significant strongholds. This fort is located on the outskirts of the Anchuthengu beach and offers panoramic views of the city. 13. Padmanabhaswamy Temple in Trivandrum It is a magnificent temple with a shining architectural design and an awe-inspiring ambience, and it is one of the top locations to see in Trivandrum. This memorial temple is also the world's costliest temple. The temple is dedicated to Lord Sri Padmanabhaswamy, who is regarded as Trivandrum's lord. The temple has a long and illustrious history. It is one of India's and the world's most-visited holy sites. The vast temple is an architectural masterpiece, with every detail built with great care and consideration. A strict clothing code is in place, and only traditional attire is permitted. 14. Attukal Temple in Trivandrum This interesting temple devoted to Goddess Bhadrakali - one of the forms of Goddess Mahakali is one of the greatest Trivandrum locations to see. This temple boasts awe-inspiring architectural architecture and a tranquil environment, making it one of the greatest tourist attractions in Trivandrum. Attukal Temple holds multiple Guinness World Records, including the most people for any celebration. Pongal festival is celebrated with tremendous zeal on the temple grounds. After visiting the temple, you may stop by a well-known Indian Coffee House for a great cup of coffee and breakfast. 15. Sree Chitra Art Gallery in Trivandrum The art gallery, founded in 1935 by the Maharaja of Travancore Sri Chitra Thirunal, is one of the top sites to visit in Trivandrum. It is a lovely destination with some wonderful items from the Kingdom of Travancore and Kerala. There are some wonderful collections of paintings, many of which were produced by royal Travancore family members. The museum also features contemporary art exhibits from art hubs in Japan, Tibet, China, and Indonesia, among other places. 16. Kanakakunnu Palace in Trivandrum It is an amazing and brilliant area built in the typical Kerala artificial design, making it one of the top Trivandrum tourist spots. This majestic mansion is close to the Napier Museum and Zoo and well preserved and tidy.