ecies include sharks, lobsters, starfish, beautiful corals, and more. The museum is well-kept, well-lit, and clean. The museum charges a fee of $20 per person to visit. 18. Aazhimala Siva Temple in Trivandrum This temple is highly colourful and devoted to Lord Shiva. The temple is well-known for its unique and breathtaking architectural features. The temple's surroundings are pretty lovely. A seashore with many rocks is located near the temple. The temple has a magnificent and massive statue of Lord Shiva. It is one of Trivandrum's famous Shiva temples. The view from this cliff is incredible. The sunrise and sunset views from here are breathtaking. It is one of the top attractions in Thiruvananthapuram. 19. Neyyar Dam in Trivandrum This dam, really the home of paradise in Kerala, is a fantastic Trivandrum sightseeing area to spend a pleasant day in the sun and is one of the best natural marvels and famous tourist destinations in Trivandrum. The dam is home to much rare flora, wildlife, and medicinal herbs that promote well-being. Immerse yourself in the positive vibes and refresh all of your senses in the magnificent surroundings. Visit this dam for a great day and have a good time. 20. Poovar Island in Trivandrum Poovar Island is a well-known island resort in Kerala surrounded by tranquil backwaters. It is a tropical paradise in the south. Imagine amazing sunset views among coconut palm trees, immaculate beaches with golden sand, dreamlike blue waters, and the sound of waves slamming on the breathtaking shoreline. If you're searching for a lovely hideaway with floating cottages constructed on stilts, this is one of the greatest cottages in Trivandrum. 21. Palace Museum Or Kuthira Malika in Trivandrum The Palace Museum is located in the Kuthiramalika Palace, established by Travancore's ruler, Maharaja Swati Thirunal Balarama Varma. The temple is on the list of top attractions in Trivandrum and is located in the fort region. It has excellent Travancore temple archite