us unique kinds of flora and wildlife in the area. 2. Sree Chitra Art Gallery in Trivandrum The Sree Chitra Art Gallery is close to the Napier Museum. This art gallery is well-known for its extensive collection of paintings by the well-known early painter Raja Ravi Varma. This art collection features paintings in the Rajput, Rajasthani, and Mughal styles. The paintings in the Chitra Art Gallery are outstanding in Balinese and Tanjore styles. These are composed of fine stonework and dark hues. It also exhibits Tibetan, Chinese, and Japanese art traditions. There is also a section dedicated to small artworks. These images will wow you. This art gallery is well-known across the world. Every day, hundreds of visitors visit. The Sree Chitra Art Gallery and its displays require at least two hours of your time. 3. Happyland Water Theme Park in Trivandrum Happyland Amusement Park is located in Vembayam, on the outskirts of Thiruvananthapuram. Flying Fox, Uphill Drive, Challenger, Crazy Cruise, Columbus, and many other pulse-racing rides are available at the amusement park to add to the fun and heartbeat. The park is designed to meet the highest safety requirements. Water World is largely intended for family enjoyment. Children's Village contains rides designed just for them. It is close to the lovely beach view. Happyland Water Theme Park is a tremendous experience for you if you seek endless fun and excitement. 4. Science and Technology Museum in Trivandrum The Napier Museum is relatively near to the Science and Technology Museum. The major goal of constructing this museum is to raise scientific knowledge among students and the general public. The Science and Technology Museum provides both a learning and entertainment facility. It is a big draw for the kids. It depicts all aspects of science and technology. It has several animated samples, effects, and electrical equipment. Bio-medical videos are also shown. This science and technology museum also features India's most advanced and technologically advanced planetarium. The entry charge is quite low here. 5. Napier Museum in Trivandrum It is an attractive museum and the ideal venue to learn about Kerala's extremely rich culture and historical history. Trivandrum's museum is a major art and cultural centre. This wonderful museum, founded in the mid-19th century by a British commander called Napier, is one of the top tourist attractions in Trivandrum. The museum displays some beautiful sculptures and coins from Kerala's past. The intriguing musical instruments from various locations and ages of Kerala are one of the museum's greatest attractions. The entrance cost is INR 20 per person. The surrounding area is rich and green. 6. Shanmugam Beach in Trivandrum Shanmugam Beach is a beautiful beach located near the city airport. This beach with pure blue sea and white sand is a great location to calm and enjoy the ethereal surroundings. The beach is very clean and has maintained its natural beauty, making it one of the greatest spots to visit in Trivandrum. On the shore, there is also a little Devi shrine. The sunset views from the beach are truly exceptional and enchanting. The peaceful beach is pretty long and quite attractive. The nicest thing about this beach is that it is not as crowded as some of the city's other famous beaches, except around sunset, when many people come here to take in the breathtaking sunset views. 7. Vellayani Lake in Trivandrum Vellayani Lake is the biggest lake in Trivandrum and one of the greatest Trivandrum tourist attractions. The lake provides stunning views of the hamlet and the backwaters, making it a terrific site to visit. Fishing lovers can also test their skills at this lake. It's a great spot for a family picnic. This lake, located in the city's rural sector, is home to white ducks and lotus blossoms. The magnificent surroundings of the lake will inspire you and make you want to spend time enjoying this wonderful lake. There are numerous things to do 