 a boat trip and enjoy the picture-perfect sunset. If you're searching for a rejuvenating getaway following a long day, Akkulam Lake has all you need! 12. Anchuthengu Fort in Trivandrum The English East India Company erected this fort in the 16th century, roughly 32 kilometres from Trivandrum Central Railway Station. It was also the East Indian Company's initial colony in Kerala and one of the Company's most significant strongholds. This fort is located on the outskirts of the Anchuthengu beach and offers panoramic views of the city. 13. Padmanabhaswamy Temple in Trivandrum It is a magnificent temple with a shining architectural design and an awe-inspiring ambience, and it is one of the top locations to see in Trivandrum. This memorial temple is also the world's costliest temple. The temple is dedicated to Lord Sri Padmanabhaswamy, who is regarded as Trivandrum's lord. The temple has a long and illustrious history. It is one of India's and the world's most-visited holy sites. The vast temple is an architectural masterpiece, with every detail built with great care and consideration. A strict clothing code is in place, and only traditional attire is permitted. 14. Attukal Temple in Trivandrum This interesting temple devoted to Goddess Bhadrakali - one of the forms of Goddess Mahakali is one of the greatest Trivandrum locations to see. This temple boasts awe-inspiring architectural architecture and a tranquil environment, making it one of the greatest tourist attractions in Trivandrum. Attukal Temple holds multiple Guinness World Records, including the most people for any celebration. Pongal festival is celebrated with tremendous zeal on the temple grounds. After visiting the temple, you may stop by a well-known Indian Coffee House for a great cup of coffee and breakfast. 15. Sree Chitra Art Gallery in Trivandrum The art gallery, founded in 1935 by the Maharaja of Travancore Sri Chitra Thirunal, is one of the top sites to visit in Trivandrum. It is a lovely destination with some wonderful items from the Kingdom of Travancore and Kerala. There are some wonderful collections of paintings, many of which were produced by royal Travancore family members. The museum also features contemporary art exhibits from art hubs in Japan, Tibet, China, and Indonesia, among other places. 16. Kanakakunnu Palace in Trivandrum It is an amazing and brilliant area built in the typical Kerala artificial design, making it one of the top Trivandrum tourist spots. This majestic mansion is close to the Napier Museum and Zoo and well preserved and tidy. The lush green beauty of the palace's environs is truly lovely. This region is serene and quiet. A fantastic spot to relax. There is also a restaurant in the royal complex where you may have a delicious cup of tea or coffee. On weekends, people bring their instruments and jam here. There are retail kiosks in the palace where you may buy local goods and handicrafts. 17. Sagarika Marine Research Aquarium in Trivandrum This little aquarium is quite famous among visitors since it houses some amazing unusual fish. Some of India's rarest fish are maintained here, and the vistas of these underwater residents will inspire you. If you are interested in underwater life and fish, you must visit this location. Fish species include sharks, lobsters, starfish, beautiful corals, and more. The museum is well-kept, well-lit, and clean. The museum charges a fee of $20 per person to visit. 18. Aazhimala Siva Temple in Trivandrum This temple is highly colourful and devoted to Lord Shiva. The temple is well-known for its unique and breathtaking architectural features. The temple's surroundings are pretty lovely. A seashore with many rocks is located near the temple. The temple has a magnificent and massive statue of Lord Shiva. It is one of Trivandrum's famous Shiva temples. The view from this cliff is incredible. The sunrise and sunset views from here are breathtaking. It is one of the top attractions in Thiruvananthapuram. 19. Neyyar Dam in Trivandrum This dam, really the home of paradise in Kerala, is a fantastic Trivandrum sightseeing area to spend a pleasant day in the sun and is one of the best natural marvels and famous tourist destinations in Trivandrum. The dam is home to much rare flora, wildlife, and medicinal herbs that promote well-being. Immerse yourself in the positive vibes and refresh all of your senses in the magnificent surroundings. Visit this dam for a great day and have a good time. 20. Poovar Island in Trivandrum Poovar Island is a well-known island resort in Kerala surrounded by tranquil backwaters. It is a tropical paradise in the south. Imagine amazing sunset views among coconut palm trees, immaculate beaches with golden sand, dreamlike blue waters, and the sound of waves slamming on the breathtaking shoreline. If you're searching for a lovely hideaway with floating cottages constructed on stilts, this is one of the greatest cottages in Trivandrum. 21. Palace Museum Or Kuthira Malika in Trivandrum The Palace Museum is located in the Kuthiramalika Palace, established by Travancore's ruler, Maharaja Swati Thirunal Balarama Varma. The temple is on the list of top attractions in Trivandrum and is located in the fort region. It has excellent Travancore temple architecture. The museum holds pictures of the royal family and other valuable treasures. The 122 wooden horse fridges placed on the museum's outside walls are the main draw for most visitors. How To Reach Trivandrum 1. By Flight Trivandrum has an airport that serves domestic and international flights. This airport has excellent connections to all major domestic and international airports. You can take a cab from the airport to your location in Trivandrum. 2. By Train Trivandrum Central Railway Station is the city's largest and busiest railway station. Several trains link to other key stations at various hours of the day. Trivandrum Railway Station is South India's third-largest railway station. 3. By Road Regular